task.summary: Default task
Finished the geometry creator for the cylinder nodes.

Augmented the cylinder node creator so that for each node it creates the following attributes: theta, radii, height, x, y, z, n, lft_nbr, rht_nbr, inr_nbr, otr_nbr, delta_theta, delta_radii, delta_height And returns the result as a data frame.

Augmented the cylinder node creator so that for each node it creates the following attributes: theta, radii, height, x, y, z, n, lft_nbr, rht_nbr, inr_nbr, otr_nbr, delta_theta, delta_radii, delta_height And returns the result as a data frame.
Bug fix Create cyl nodes function Outer neighbors were populating with the outer neighbors of the nodes above and below in other layers. Fixed so they now only populate with nodes from their layer.
Bug fix Added exception to procedure to export the node network dataframe so if the file is open it'll pass. Removed background for testing 3d plot.
Modified the functions to build the cylinder by component (wall, liquid, gas).
Modified the functions to build the cylinder by component (wall, liquid, gas).
Bug fixes and tuned executable builder to keep console open for debugging.
Edited the exe builder metadata.
Fixed an error in the p1 calculation, it wasn't dividing by area to get W/m2.

Changed the behavior at the outermost and innermost nodes so that, when those nodes are calculated, it pretends that there is one more layer of nodes at a temperature identical to the current temperature of the node. Aka, for the outermost node, it assumes that there is no heat transfer to the outside.
Last commit before changing the view factoring process.

Major changes across the board. Reorganized the code into multiple Python files by category. Coded and improved graphics output. Added convection boundary condition all the way around the cylinder shell wall.

Major changes across the board. Reorganized the code into multiple Python files by category. Coded and improved graphics output. Added convection boundary condition all the way around the cylinder shell wall.
Changed the cylinder creating main function and partial functions so that they are able to generate the other cylinder components again (gas layers and cylinder wall).
Fresh push since the last overhaul, which was to bastardized my code to generate those Temperature vs h-value plots that Budiman wanted.
Working on the functions for assigning d1, d2, and d3 parameters for the cylindrical heat diffusion between heterogeneous nodes. Not finished.
